title: Multiple Errors when using analyze_videos()
body:
**OS: Windows 10,  deeplabcut: 2.0.5**

**Anaconda Env (dlc as recommnded by this GitHub)**


**Problem**

After doing some label refining and retraining, I am attempting to analyse the video having evaluated the network. However, no matter the videos I am looking at I receive the following errors (abridged but one can find the full error print out below).

The key parts are as follows:
```FileNotFoundError: File F:\DeepLabTrial\DeepLabCut_trial_dogs\videos\dog35DeepCut_resnet50_Dogs_Data_Generation_30Apr9shuffle1_85000.h5 does not exist```
and
```UnknownError: Failed to get convolution algorithm. This is probably because cuDNN failed to initialize, so try looking to see if a warning log message was printed above.
	 [[{{node resnet_v1_50/conv1/Conv2D}} = Conv2D[T=DT_FLOAT, data_format="NCHW", dilations=[1, 1, 1, 1], padding="VALID", strides=[1, 1, 2, 2], use_cudnn_on_gpu=true, _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:GPU:0"](resnet_v1_50/conv1/Conv2D-0-TransposeNHWCToNCHW-LayoutOptimizer, resnet_v1_50/conv1/weights/read)]]
```

Admittedly, as I attempt this analysis my laptop is currently performing some retraining for another video so I feel this is quite likely to be the source of the errors mentioned. If this is the case I will close the issue myself.

Any help would be greatly appreciated.
